## Abstract Interfaces in Core and Renderer

The following interfaces are declared in `Pigeon/Core/` and `Pigeon/Renderer/` and implemented by platform code.

### `pg::Window` — `Pigeon/Core/Window.h`

```cpp
namespace pg {

    struct WindowProps {
        std::string Title;
        unsigned int Width;   // default 1280
        unsigned int Height;  // default 720
    };

    class PIGEON_API Window {
    public:
        using EventCallbackFn = std::function<void(Event&)>;

        struct Data {
            const char* m_Title = "Windows Window";
            EventCallbackFn EventCallback;
        };

        virtual void OnUpdate() = 0;
        virtual void Shutdown() = 0;
        virtual unsigned int GetWidth() const = 0;
        virtual unsigned int GetHeight() const = 0;
        inline void SetEventCallback(const EventCallbackFn& callback);
        virtual void SetVSync(bool enabled) = 0;
        virtual bool IsVSync() const = 0;
        virtual void* GetNativeWindow() const = 0;
        virtual void* GetGraphicsContext() const = 0;

        // Factory — implementation chosen by TESTS_ENABLED at link time
        static pg::S_Ptr<Window> Create(const WindowProps& props = WindowProps());
    protected:
        static Data m_Data;   // shared across all instances
    };
}
```

The `static Data m_Data` member is defined once per translation unit:
- In `WindowsWindow.cpp` when `TESTS_ENABLED` is **not** defined.
- In `TestingWindow.cpp` when `TESTS_ENABLED` **is** defined.

### `pg::PlatformInput` — `Pigeon/Core/Input.h`

```cpp
namespace pg {
    class PIGEON_API PlatformInput {
    public:
        // Public — called by InputSystem to translate platform codes to engine codes
        inline static unsigned char GetKeyCode(unsigned char keyCode);
        inline static unsigned char GetMouseButtonCode(unsigned char keyCode);

    protected:
        // Protected — only reachable by the engine, not game code
        inline static bool IsKeyPressed(int keycode);
        inline static bool IsMouseButtonPressed(int button);
        inline static std::pair<float, float> GetMousePosition();
        inline static float GetMouseX();
        inline static float GetMouseY();
        inline static PlatformInput& GetInput();

        virtual bool IsKeyPressedImpl(int keycode) = 0;
        virtual bool IsMouseButtonPressedImpl(int button) = 0;
        virtual std::pair<float, float> GetMousePositionImpl() = 0;
        virtual float GetMouseXImpl() = 0;
        virtual float GetMouseYImpl() = 0;
        virtual unsigned char GetKeyCodeImpl(unsigned char keyCode) = 0;
        virtual unsigned char GetMouseButtonCodeImpl(unsigned char keyCode) = 0;
    private:
        // Singleton — implementation set by TESTS_ENABLED at link time
        static pg::S_Ptr<PlatformInput> s_Instance;
    };
}
```

The singleton `s_Instance` is initialised once:
- `std::make_shared<pg::WindowsInput>()` in `WindowsInput.cpp` when `TESTS_ENABLED` is not defined.
- `std::make_shared<pg::TestingInput>()` in `TestingInput.cpp` when `TESTS_ENABLED` is defined.

