## Preprocessor Guards

| Symbol | Defined by | Effect |
|---|---|---|
| `PG_PLATFORM_WINDOWS` | CMake (`target_compile_definitions`) when `WIN32` is true | Enables the `PIGEON_API` dllexport/import macros; gates `EntryPoint.h`; is the only supported platform (Core.h emits `#error` on anything else) |
| `PG_PLATFORM_UNIX` | CMake when `UNIX` is true | Defined in CMakeLists but unreachable — `Core.h` `#error`s before it could be used |
| `TESTS_ENABLED` | CMake under the `Testing` configuration (`-DTESTS_ENABLED`) | Switches factory functions (`Window::Create`, `PlatformInput::s_Instance`) from Windows to Testing implementations; disables `PG_DEBUGBREAK` (so assertion failures in tests do not call `__debugbreak`); disables `ImGuiLayer` creation; exposes `Application::GetData()` and `Application::TestUpdate()` |
| `PG_DYNAMIC_LINK` | Not set by the current CMakeLists | When set together with `PG_BUILD_DLL`, enables dllexport; otherwise `PIGEON_API` expands to nothing (static library, current default) |
| `PG_BUILD_DLL` | CMake (`target_compile_definitions`) when `WIN32` | Combined with `PG_DYNAMIC_LINK` to select dllexport; currently harmless because `PG_DYNAMIC_LINK` is not set |

The `#ifndef TESTS_ENABLED` / `#ifdef TESTS_ENABLED` guards in `.cpp` files are the sole mechanism for selecting between implementations at link time. There are no runtime branches.

